{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17528281","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17528281"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T15:40:10+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T15:40:10+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14284"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14284","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14284"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.07,0.84,0.02,0.06,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6979"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"104332"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"6979","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6979"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14284"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86661"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"37"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"675"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"1063"},{"type":"tags","id":"1804"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"2545"},{"type":"tags","id":"2546"},{"type":"tags","id":"4097"},{"type":"tags","id":"4640"},{"type":"tags","id":"4966"},{"type":"tags","id":"4983"},{"type":"tags","id":"4991"},{"type":"tags","id":"11622"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11643"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"16468"},{"type":"contributions","id":"34430"},{"type":"contributions","id":"37525"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44414"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"104332","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/104332"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 28-year-old Aboriginal man from a remote community in the Northern Territory presents to the General Practice clinic with a three-week history of a non-itchy rash. He also reports fatigue, mild fever, and generalised aches. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. He works as a bus driver. He reports unprotected sexual intercourse with more than one partner in the past six months.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears well. His pulse rate is 82/min, blood pressure 125/75 mmHg, respiratory rate 16/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 37.8\u00b0C. There is a copper-coloured maculopapular rash on his trunk and extremities, including his palms and soles. An image of this rash is shown below. There are several painless, enlarged lymph nodes in his neck and groin. Condylomata lata is noted around the anus.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate treatment?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Aciclovir","Benzathine benzylpenicillin","Metronidazole","Phenoxymethylpenicillin","Albendazole"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with classic features of secondary syphilis, including a copper-coloured maculopapular rash involving palms and soles, generalised lymphadenopathy, condylomata lata, and constitutional symptoms. Secondary syphilis is the systemic stage of syphilis infection (caused by \u003Cem\u003ETreponema pallidum\u003C/em\u003E) occurring at the same time as or up to six months after resolution of the primary chancre. Patients with secondary syphilis are highly infectious.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBenzathine benzylpenicillin\u003C/strong\u003E is the gold standard treatment for early syphilis (primary, secondary, and early latent). A single intramuscular dose of 2.4 million units is curative in early syphilis. This treatment has excellent efficacy and has been the mainstay of therapy for decades.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAciclovir\u003C/strong\u003E is an antiviral medication used for herpes simplex virus infections. While genital herpes can cause ulceration, it does not cause the systemic symptoms and characteristic rash seen in this patient as a result of secondary syphilis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMetronidazole\u003C/strong\u003E is used for treating anaerobic bacterial infections and protozoal infections such as trichomoniasis. It would not be effective against \u003Cem\u003ET. pallidum\u003C/em\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPhenoxymethylpenicillin\u003C/strong\u003E is an oral penicillin that does not achieve adequate tissue levels for treating syphilis. Benzathine benzylpenicillin is specifically required for its long-acting properties.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAlbendazole\u003C/strong\u003E is an antihelmintic and would not be effective against \u003Cem\u003ET. pallidum.\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPeople in remote Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander communities in Northern Australia have much higher notification rates of sexually transmitted infections. Advise no sexual contact for seven days after treatment, and no sex with partners from the last three months (if primary syphilis) or six months (if secondary syphilis) until partners have been tested and treated if necessary. Syphilis is a nationally notifiable condition. It is imperative these cases are reported to the local public health unit.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Secondary syphilis typically presents with a generalised copper-coloured maculopapular rash, lymphadenopathy, and constitutional symptoms.","A single intramuscular dose of benzathine benzylpenicillin (2.4 million units) is the recommended treatment for early syphilis.","Cultural sensitivity and contact tracing are especially essential components of sexually transmitted infection management in Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples."],"references":["Remote Primary Health Care Manuals. Tropical Health Orientation Manual. Alice Springs, NT: Centre for Remote Health; 2020."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86661"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14284"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21179"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21179","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21179"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/MhCIEbfI3fwfhEjnwDw9lXPI4KOMDP.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/MhCIEbfI3fwfhEjnwDw9lXPI4KOMDP.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":503,"height":435}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86661","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/86661"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-06-01T03:08:30+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-01T03:11:10+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6979"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"104332"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udda0","name":"Infectious Diseases","synonyms":["ID"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2021-05-21T07:51:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"37","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/37"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf46","name":"Sexual Health","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Mana